 ortalimages/portalimages/cb1ee9cf-dc61-4c69-82eb-f2684b83aafd.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Shop and explore the beauty of orchids. Multiple displays of o
 rchids from the rarest of species to cultivated hybrids will be artistical
 ly arranged. Individual orchids in 128 classes will vie for ribbons. Twent
 y-five entries will receive "best of class" green ribbons\, and the best-a
 ppointed plant in the show will receive the Chicago Horticultural Society 
 Award from the American Orchid Society judges. Several orchid vendors will
  also be on-site selling many orchid varieties. Supplies and equipment\, b
 ooks\, pins\, clothing and the society's custom bark mix and fertilizer al
 so for sale. Visit the  Illinois Orchid Society's website Location: Burnst
 ein Hall\, Linnaeus & Pullman Rooms
