BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Arath Herce & HUMBE
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T000000
UID:260307amUhncH-cEyxXeC7yqOIUw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/u23Zf7SR5U6FTDRXZgdIpw.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Humbe\, the Mexican singer\, songwriter\, and producer\, began
  his journey into music at the age of 9\, ignited by an old Yamaha keyboar
 d that became the portal to his artistic exploration.\n\nInfluenced by R&B
  and Pop\, Humbe's music resonates with soulful melodies and captivating t
 unes. Yet\, it's his genuine connection with his and other people’s feel
 ings that truly sets him apart when it comes to creating music. Each song 
 echoes the sentiments of a shared experience\, fostering a close-knit comm
 unity around his work.\n\nIn 2021\, after receiving critical and people’
 s praise for his 2nd album ENTROPÍA\, Humbe celebrated his 1st Latin GRAM
 MY nomination for Best New Artist\, with the release of his self-written a
 nd produced album AURORA\, which consolidated him as one of the most solid
  uprising artists within the Latin music scene.\n\nBut beyond the glare\, 
 Humbe remains dedicated to his craft\, continuously evolving as an artist.
  His commitment to creating heartfelt\, relatable music reflects not only 
 his artistic talent but also the unwavering support of his loyal fanbase\,
  making his music a comforting presence in the lives of his listeners\, wh
 ich led to his most personal album to date: ESENCIA\n\nAs Humbe prepares t
 o embark on his next tour\, his natural urge to connect keeps manifesting 
 through the creation of music. In late 2023 he released «BIEN HECHO»\, 
 «PATADAS DE AHOGADO» along LATIN MAFIA\, and the endearing viral hit «
 FANTASMAS» as further proof of his sensitivity to the world around him.
LOCATION:The Salt Shed Indoors (Shed)
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/1037377444?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=2
 87&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunny Akhigbe presents: Nourish for Life: A Community Nutrition Ta
 lk
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T150000
UID:260303IduVE_bHJ02Y2qReGl3laA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/7M-KCgYK00yYFk5FH6Alpg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Wild Onion Market\, in partnership with Sunny Akhigbe of the A
  Boy and His Dream Foundation\, is pleased to present a free community eve
 nt\, *Nourish for Life: A Community Nutrition Talk*\, on Saturday\, March
  14\, from 2 to 3 p.m. \n\nThe presentation will be at Wild Onion Market 
 a community-owned grocery store at 7007 N Clark in Rogers Park.\n\nSunny A
 khigbe is the founder of A Boy and His Dream\, a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedic
 ated to creating opportunities for underserved youth through education\, m
 entorship\, nutrition\, and community support\, both locally in Chicago an
 d internationally in Nigeria. He will lead this informative session focuse
 d on practical\, accessible approaches to healthy eating.\n\nMr Akhigbe\, 
 a native of Nigeria\, now calls Chicago home. He is a business professiona
 l with an MBA from Purdue University and also a certified fitness coach. C
 omplementing his philanthropic work\, he is a powerful motivational speake
 r.\n\nHis talk will explore how to eat well within real-world constraints 
 such as cost\, access\, and time. Topics include selecting wholesome foods
  on a budget and making everyday food choices that support long-term healt
 h for individuals and families.\n\nThis event is free and open to the publ
 ic. Attendees will have the opportunity to engage directly with Mr. Akhigb
 e\, ask questions\, and leave with actionable insights for better nourishm
 ent and wellbeing.\n\n**Event Details** **What:** Nourish for Life: A Com
 munity Nutrition Talk with Sunny Akhigbe **When:** Saturday\, March 14\, 
 2026\, 2 to 3 p.m. **Where:** Wild Onion Market\, 7007 N Clark St.\, Chic
 ago\, IL 60626 **Cost:** Free\n\nLearn more about A Boy and His Dream at 
 www.aboyandhisdream.org\, and about Wild Onion Market at wildonionmarket.c
 om.
LOCATION:Wild Onion Market community grocery store
URL:https://wildonionmarket.com/event/nourish-for-life-a-community-nutriti
 on-talk/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
