UID:260227w_g_6W5Y2E2quDZqzlfy1g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GNvy5oxRZkODTjkRyc7o5Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on March 14 from 3 to 5 p.m. at Trinity Lutheran Churc
 h\, 3637 Golf Road\, Evanston\, for an afternoon of public community singi
 ng — learning and singing songs together as a practice of courage\, soli
 darity\, and hope. Singing in community steadies our breath\, strengthens 
 our bonds\, and helps us remember that we belong to one another. It also p
 repares us for faithful\, public\, nonviolent witness. \n\nThis gathering
  is non-partisan and deeply political\, in that it expresses our vision 
 for a world of peace and justice for all our neighbors\, near and far. \
 n\nHosted by Trinity Lutheran Church\, this event is open to people of eve
 ry religious tradition and those with no religious commitments at all who 
 share that vision. No musical background is needed. If you can breathe\, y
 ou can sing! \n\nA donation will be invited. All proceeds benefit mutual 
 aid networks in Minneapolis-St. Paul. You can register online here: https
 ://app.tickettailor.com/events/commonpulse/2081933
LOCATION:Trinity Lutheran Church
URL:https://www.trinityevanston.org/events/sing-a-better-future-into-exist
 ence
