BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Refracted Theatre Company Presents “Dream Hou$e\,” September 1
 2 - October 8
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T220000
UID:250829xrbattMK2kObcCOtIbRZjw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/7eg-tBbLT0Ctc2DQ2dc_HA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Award-winning Refracted Theatre Company presents Dream Hou$e\,
  written by Eliana Pipes and directed by Laura Alcalá Baker\, September 1
 2 – October 18\, at the Den Theatre\, 1331 N Milwaukee Ave.  \n\nTwo si
 sters are appearing on an HGTV-style reality show to sell their family hom
 e\, hoping to capitalize on the gentrification in their “changing neighb
 orhood.” As they perform for the camera the show starts to slip into the
  surreal: one sister grapples with turmoil in the family’s ancestral pas
 t and the other learns how much she’s willing to sacrifice for the famil
 y’s future. Dream Hou$e\, which earned both the Kendeda Award and Steinb
 erg Playwriting Award in 2021\, is a crowd-pleasing comedy with a twist th
 at asks: What is the cultural cost of progress in America? And is cashing 
 in always selling out? \n\nPreviews are Friday\, Sept. 12 at 7:30 p.m.\, S
 aturday\, Sept. 13 at 7:30 p.m.\, Sunday\, Sept. 14 at 6 p.m. and Wednesda
 y\, Sept. 17 at 7:30 p.m.The regular performance schedule is Thursdays –
  Saturdays at 7:30 p.m. and Sundays at 3 p.m. Tickets go on sale Tuesday\,
  July 29 for $12 \\(previews\\) – $40\, before handling fees\, and may b
 e purchased at RefractedCo.com.
LOCATION:The Den Theatre
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/refracted-theatre-company-presents-drea
 m-houe-september-12-october-8/2026-03-14/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
