SUMMARY:Imagine U: Theatre for the Very Young presents
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T134500
UID:250730xTtTY53v1kqhce98P6psGw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Bb7QdBctkUiAy4nAdyT09Q.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a vibrant and engaging introduction to the magic o
 f theatre\, specially designed for children aged 2-5 and their grown-ups. 
 Two different remounted shows will take place: *Imagine That!* (3/7 and 
 3/15) and *Splish\, Splash: A Day on the Lake* (3/8 and 3/14).\n\nOur mu
 lti-sensory performances offer a delightful first taste of live theatre\, 
 crafted by a dedicated team of educational artists who specialize in early
  childhood development alongside undergraduate students focused on theatre
  for young audiences. Come and experience the joy of interactive storytell
 ing and creative exploration with your little ones!\n\nImagine That!\n\nAu
 tumn\, Winter\, and Spring are on a mission to make a rainbow\, but they n
 eed the help of Summer—that’s you! In this interactive\, multi-sensory
  adventure\, preschool audiences will use the power of their imagination t
 o bring the colors of the seasons to life.\n\nApproximate run time: 45 min
 utes Suggested ages: 2-5\n\nSplish\, Splash: A Day on the Lake\n\nSet sail
  on a magical journey around Lake Michigan! Through music\, puppetry\, and
  interactive experiences\, our crew of young sailors will explore the wild
 life and whimsy of the lake.\n\nApproximate run time: 45 minutes Suggested
  ages: 2-5
LOCATION:Northwestern University - Hal & Martha Hyer Wallis Theater
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/imagine-u-theatre-for-the-very-young/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
