DESCRIPTION:Death is a fact of life: horses get turned into glue\, cows ge
 t sucked into tornadoes reverse-alien-style\, and even pop legend Michael 
 Jackson can’t live forever. It’s a bummer\, but we have the perfect so
 lution: a brand new laugh-out-loud comedy show that invites you to escape 
 your own mortality by celebrating life in all its weirdness.  \n\nGoodbye
  Darkness\, We’re Not Friends is THE sketch comedy show of the season. F
 eaturing a stellar cast of female and nonbinary performers\, Goodbye Darkn
 ess challenges comedy norms and dares to venture off the beaten path. Join
  us this March for the perfect show to transition from the darkness of win
 ter into the brightness of spring \n\n  \n\nCreated by Sophie Levinson  
 \n\nWith Sarah Welford \n\n  \n\nFeaturing: \n\nIzzy Baker \n\nAnna Goodi
 n \n\nSerena Daley \n\nSophie Levinson \n\nJenny Paez \n\nSarah Welford \n
 \n  \n\nWritten by Sophie Levinson  \n\nDirected by Sarah Welford \n\n 
LOCATION:The Second City - de Maat Studio Theatre
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/goodbye-darkness-were-not-friends/
 2026-03-15/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
