SUMMARY:Pastimes Pokemon TCG League Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T120000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T163000
UID:260211xq9l1-XRLU6nsPCZT81I5g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/cec9f78e-7b92-4b10-94ba-030d00b441ec.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Pokémon TCG League Challenge\n\nDescription:\n\nGet started w
 ith Pokémon TCG play at League Challenge tournaments. League Challenges a
 re small\, entry-level events that are held monthly. At Pokémon TCG Leagu
 e Challenge tournaments\, players can earn Championship Points and work to
 ward earning an invitation to the World Championships! These events are de
 signed to be a player's first experience of formal tournament competition 
 before moving up to League Cups\, Regional Championships\, and beyond.\n\n
 League Challenge events are open to all players. Players must bring their 
 own legal 60-card Standard Format deck\, damage counters\, and a randomize
 r \\(translucent die\, official Pokémon coin\, etc.\\).League Challenges 
 use Standard Swiss rounds of 30 minutes plus 3 turns\; this event has no t
 op cut. The number of rounds will be based on the number of players in the
  event.\n\nEvent Details:\n\nRegistration: 12:00 pm\n\nStart Time: 12:30 p
 m\n\nEntry: $12\n\nRules Enforcement: Requires player deck lists\n\nFormat
 : Swiss Rounds\n\nPrizes:\n\nPrizes are awarded to the top players in each
  of the three age divisions. To earn points and prizes\, players must have
  a Pokémon Trainer Club account with a Player ID attached and must have o
 pted into the Play! Pokémon program. All participants will receive 1\n\nP
 lay! Point\n\njust for playing.\n\nIn addition\, each player will receive 
 a Play! Pokémon prizes pack \\(while supplies last\\) plus $4 store credi
 t for participation. $8 store credit per participant will go into the priz
 e pool\, and the top players will receive prizes based on standings.\n\n1s
 t Place: 15 Championship points\n\n2nd Place: 12 Championship points\n\n3r
 d & 4th Place: 10 Championship points\n\n5th - 8th Place: 8 Championship p
 oints \\(requires 21 participants\\)\n\nContact Information:\n\nIf you hav
 e questions\, you can email\n\nannika@pastimes.net\n\nor join the Pastimes
  Discord Server \\(  discord.gg/WQHa3mf \\)\n\n\\*All event details\, entr
 y fees\, and prizes are subject to change.\n\nRefund Policy:\n\nTickets ar
 e refundable up to 7 DAYS BEFORE THE EVENT. After that\, tickets are non-r
 efundable.\\*
LOCATION:Pastimes Comics & Games
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/pastimes-pokemon-tcg-l
 eague-challenge/18110150/2026-03-15T12
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The 8th Dwarf
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
UID:260206J6DhWRdxg0e3ieXIhxf2nw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/pitgL2K1EkmN36CFvAZoFQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Binkley\, an outsider dwarf from the Kingdom of Magical Land\,
  is quiet\, timid and scared of the dark — not exactly the best characte
 ristics for working in a mine\, the job to which all dwarves aspire. \n\nB
 ut inspired by the kindness and motherly affection of Snow White\, Binkley
  goes on a quest to find three items that will assure them a place amongst
  the dwarf elite. Will Binkley find the courage that resides deep inside t
 hem? Will they be paralyzed by the Wicked Witch? Will they be able to find
  a genuine cow? \n\nThe 8th Dwarf is a story of the power of courage\, ki
 ndness and wit\, and how those characteristics mean more than all the mate
 rial goods in the world. \n\nThe 8th Dwarf is part of our Nightlight yo
 ung audiences series\, which produces original\, adapted and forgotten pla
 ys geared toward children and the adults who love them. The show takes pla
 ce on Saturdays and Sundays at 2 p.m. from February 7-15. More information
  is available on the show page.
LOCATION:Bughouse Theater
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/the-8th-dwarf/2026-03-15/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
