BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:20-Hour Foundations of Equity Training
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T150000
UID:2602245jqN1L1agkOYI4vd1SjZig
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/1fcs4Gc_s0mrZCK5PC0LxQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore is offering **a powerful\, 20-hour 
 foundational equity training designed specifically for leaders who shape w
 orkplaces\, institutions\, and communities.**\n\nThis is a structured\, in
 -depth learning experience that equips leaders with historical understandi
 ng\, practical tools\, and relational skills needed to lead more equitably
  and effectively in today’s complex environments. *There is special pri
 cing available for Nonprofit professionals and Educators.*\n\n**Why Equity
  Training?**\n\nCommunities and organizations are facing major change\, he
 ightened expectations around equity\, and increasingly diverse teams. Lead
 ers are being called to respond with clarity\, confidence\, and competence
 .\n\nThis training helps participants:\n\nUnderstand the historical roots 
 of systemic inequities and how they continue to shape present-day systems\
 n\nIdentify how policies\, practices\, and cultural norms can reinforce in
 equity or strengthen equity\n\nStrengthen an ability to lead across differ
 ences and change\n\nDevelop practical strategies for creating inclusive\, 
 accountable spaces\n\n**Who This Is For:**\n\nWhether you lead a nonprofit
 \, manage a department\, chair a board\, or convene a professional network
 \, this training provides foundational knowledge and applied tools that tr
 anslate directly into your leadership practice.\n\nThis program represents
  a significant value for organizations seeking meaningful professional dev
 elopment without the cost of private consulting engagements!\n\n**NOTE:** 
 This training can be used toward ICDVP CEUs for professionals working in d
 omestic violence prevention.\n\n*Seats are limited.*\n\nIf your organizati
 on is committed to leading with integrity\, strengthening culture\, and se
 rving your community more equitably\, this is the right opportunity for yo
 u.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n**DATE/TIME:** March 16th\, 2026 - March 20th\, 
 2026 (M-F) from 10am -3pm CST\n\n**PRICE:** $200 for standard ticketing pe
 r person\, $150 for Nonprofit Professionals and Educators\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\
 \_\n\n**QUESTIONS…? CONTACT:**\n\nRoger Moreano\, Senior Director of Ins
 titutional and Community Equity\n\nrmoreano@ywca-ens.org\n\n847-864-8445 e
 xt. 1128
LOCATION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/20-hour-foundations-of-equity-training-ti
 ckets-1983364569819?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-medi
 um=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
