 e. \n\nSynopsis\n\nTeenager Ellie Blake and her mother Katherine do not ge
 t along\, which is why it doesn’t help when Ellie and Katherine switch b
 odies! Now \\(the day before Katherine’s wedding\\)\, Ellie and Katherin
 e must learn to understand each other before they are stuck in each other
 ’s bodies forever. Based on the classic novel and films of the same name
 \, Freaky Friday brings all the humor and heart of the original story to t
 he stage in this musical adaptation. Come join us! \n\nAuditions\n\nAuditi
 ons for Freaky Friday: A New Musical will be held March 16 from 5:30-8:30 
 pm. Callbacks \\(if necessary\\) will be held on March 17 and 18 from 7:15
 -8:30 pm. All registrants should fill out the Google form at the bottom of
  their registration receipt to schedule an audition appointment. All parti
 cipants will be assigned an audition time on a rolling basis beginning on 
 Monday\, March 16. \n\nRegister Now \n\n  \n\nPerformances\n\nPerformance
 s will be held at either Field Middle School or Northbrook Public Library 
 while Northbrook Community Center is closed for renovations on May 15 and 
 16 at 7pm\, and May 17 at 2pm.
LOCATION:Techny Prairie Activity Center
URL:https://www.nbparks.org/event/auditions-for-freaky-friday-a-new-musica
 l/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
