BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beatrice | Ruth Poor
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T160000
UID:2602179doBVIgs-0eeRiSJ_lr2xw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/LWznMwws6U-NK01KN5n0gA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:**On view February 21 - March 18\, 2026**\n\n**Opening Recept
 ion Sunday\, February 22\, 2026\, 1-4 pm**\n\n*Ruth L. Poor\, raised in In
 diana\, uses their work to dissect memories of the rural Midwest and to in
 vestigate intersections between power\, American history\, faith\, and dev
 iancy. Poor received their MFA from the Painting & Drawing department at t
 he School of the Art Institute of Chicago (SAIC) and completed their B.A. 
 in Studio Art and Religious Studies at Cornell College and DePauw Universi
 ty. They currently reside in Chicago\, Illinois\, where they teach at SAIC
 \, North Central College\, and College of DuPage\, and teach/advise with t
 he Prison + Neighborhood Arts Project. They have shown work nationally and
  internationally at venues such as the University ofChicago \\[Chicago\, I
 L\\]\, Secrist|Beach Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, the New York Academy of 
 Art \\[New York\, NY\\]\, Zolla/Lieberman Gallery\\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, Art 
 EXPO \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, The Green Gallery \\[Milwaukee\, WI\\]\, ADDS DO
 NNA Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, Manifest Gallery\\[Cincinnati\, OH\\]\, W
 oman Made Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, and Indiana University \\[Bloomingt
 on\, IN\\]. They are also a current Artist-in-Residence with the Chicago A
 rtist Coalition (2024-2026).*
LOCATION:Evanston Art Center
URL:https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/woundwomb-ruth-poor
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:An Evening with Mark Oppenheimer Featuring Judy Blume: A Life
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T183000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T193000
UID:2602177zASVU5LdECZhwuk0JNNQQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/9CWM1fBljE--44K0ZZvGfQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Book Stall \\(811 Elm Street in Winnetka\\) welcomes Mark
  Oppenheimer to the store on Tuesday\, March 17 at 6:30 pm for a discussi
 on featuring his new book\, Judy Blume: A Life\, the highly anticipated bi
 ography of one of the world’s most treasured literary voices. In Judy B
 lume\, journalist\, historian\, and longtime Blume aficionado Mark Oppenhe
 imer pens a beautiful\, multidimensional portrait of the acclaimed author 
 through extensive interviews with Blume herself\, invaluable access to her
  papers and correspondence\, and thoughtful analysis of Blume’s beloved 
 novels\, including early\, unpublished works that shed light on the pathbr
 eaking writer she would become. A true gift for anyone who grew up readin
 g and loving these extraordinary books! Mark will be in-conversation with
  Betsy Bird. \n\nMark Oppenheimer is the author of four critically accl
 aimed books\, including Squirrel Hill\, Wisenheimer\, and Thirteen and 
 a Day. He has taught at NYU\, Stanford\, Yale\, and Washington University 
 in St. Louis\, where he is Professor of Practice. Mark lives with his fami
 ly in New Haven\, Connecticut.\n\nOur conversation partner Betsy Bird is
  an author\, librarian\, reviewer of children’s literature\, public spea
 ker\, and podcaster \\(not necessarily in that order\\). She is the author
  of numerous picture books\, two books for kids ages 9–12\, two books fo
 r adults about children’s books\, and more. She currently resides in Eva
 nston with her two kids\, husband\, and cats Izzy and Hilo \\(named after 
 the graphic novel series by Judd Winick\\).
LOCATION:The Book Stall
URL:https://thebookstall.com/event/2026-03-17/evening-mark-oppenheimer-fea
 turing-judy-blume-life
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
