SUMMARY:What Impact Does Income Equality Have on our Democracy? (Hybrid)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T143000
UID:260222TIYYJcNZXkOxGx8apLqWZw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/9N4Yq1N6jEawBMSR7fIYSQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:In the current moment\, there is a lot of discussion about mas
 sive accumulation of wealth among a very few. Julie Strauss explores what 
 impact\, if any\, this has on our politics and the democratic process. She
  examines whether income disparity in democratic societies pose threats. D
 oes extreme wealth contribute to polarization and cynicism toward governme
 nt institutions\, and what might the remedies be?
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
