 al of Miles Davis’ birth with a complete performance of his landmark alb
 um\, “The Birth of the Cool.” Culled from a multitude of source materi
 al\, the nonet will be performing the actual arrangements as orchestrated 
 by the likes of Gil Evans\, John Lewis\, Gerry Mulligan\, and others.\n\nC
 had McCullough\, trumpet\; Dan Nicholson\, alto sax\; Ryan Schulz\, bass t
 rumpet\; Momo Hasselbring Seko\, French horn\; Ted Hogarth\, baritone sax\
 ; John Blane\, tuba\; Kevin Fort\, piano\; Joe Policastro\, bass\; Todd Ho
 well\, drums.\n\nThis concert is generously sponsored by the Music Perfor
 mance Trust Fund \\(MPTF\\).\n\nThe event is free and open to the public.\
