 ortalimages/portalimages/713287c2-ea40-46d9-9bd5-2e196e6c0bac.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Daniel Immerwahr\, award winning professor of U.S. history at 
 Northwestern University\, will lecture on the context of the U.S./Israeli 
 war in Iran. Author of the influential book\, *How to Hide and Empire*\, I
 mmerwahr is known both for his trenchant analysis and for his wit. Refresh
 ments will be served. The talk will be followed by question and answers\, 
 as well as group discussion. It is free and open to the public. Attendees 
 are encouraged to RSVP at tinyurl.com/CAPA-March-21.
