BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vivid Art Gallery February Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T110000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T170000
UID:260203NxhLhNO0vkmTaKmIu1lkew
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/frCMskMTIE6mrpAgK-8e-w.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Vivid Art Gallery is hosting a special exhibit featuring the w
 ork of represented artist Matthew Schaefer. Entitled Journey of Intention
 \, it will show a variety of his newest work. Schaefer is an Evanston art
 ist who can be seen around town drawing in his sketch book. He then transl
 ates his sketches to inform his paintings\, which are created spontaneousl
 y\, with each brushstroke influencing the next. This exhibit is a collecti
 on of those works\, depicting scenes from the lakefront to the bustling do
 wntown. Please note that there will not be an opening for this exhibit. 
 \n\nAs the show’s title suggests\, the exhibit reflects an artistic jour
 ney that Schaefer has embarked on in recent months\, as his art continues 
 to develop in new ways. However\, as with much of his art\, the paintings
  in the exhibit are large scale and colorful\, drawing viewers into the wo
 rk. While this show encompasses urban and lakeside scenes\, Schaefer also
  creates more nature-oriented abstract landscapes as well as minimalistic 
 abstract works. \n\nPlease stop by the gallery on Saturdays only during t
 he month of February to see this beautiful work!
LOCATION:Vivid Art Gallery
URL:http://vividartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
