BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Make America Great Again -  A Short History of American Fascism
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260312Ydv7e4QObEWMrC7tb88sLg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/mad7iZ1NUU6KE3IXUL66gw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:One Year of Trump 2.0 How did we get here?!\n\nMake America Gr
 eat Again - A Short History of American Fascism from the Ku Klux Klan to t
 he Age of Trump\n\nJohn Donoghue\, an associate professor of history at Lo
 yola University Chicago is leading this forum based on a lecture he gave a
 t Loyola University late last year and his new book project *American Insu
 rrections: An Unruly History of White Nationalism*\, which traces how insu
 rrectionary violence established white supremacy in the colonial era and p
 layed a vital part in its transition to white nationalism in the United St
 ates and the resurgence of white Christian supremacy after the Civil War. 
 As the book concludes\, paramilitary violence became the strategic acceler
 ant in white Christian nationalism's passage into American fascism in the 
 twentieth and twenty-first centuries.His earlier work has focused on the h
 istory of early American colonialism\, radical political thought and actio
 n\, slavery and servitude\, abolition\, and the political economy of capit
 alism. His earlier work focused on the history of early American coloniali
 sm\, radical political thought and action\, slavery and servitude\, abolit
 ion\, and the political economy of capitalism. The event is sponsored by 
 Refuse Fascism Chicago and is endorsed by Northside Friends Meeting Minist
 ry on Racism Committee and Evanston Neighbors for Peace.
LOCATION:Evanston Public Library\, Falcon Room\, third floor
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/make-america-great-aga
 in-a-short-history-of-american-fascism/18314138/2026-03-22T14
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
