 ortalimages/portalimages/_vTuJkmzBEaWqdlnjb_wRg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:OFF NIGHTS AT THE SOMETIME CAFÉ is a campy parody of a noir m
 ystery that follows a cafe pianist in lieu of a detective. As this narrato
 r plays his way through the show\, he guides the audience through the tang
 led web of attraction\, seduction\, and general silliness that occurs when
  a bunch of attractive queer people end up in the same place. Dave Walther
 ’s Off-Nights at the Sometimes Café is a delightful\, poignantly unse
 rious celebration of queer joy and desire.
LOCATION:Bramble Arts Loft
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/off-nights-at-the-some
 time-cafe/18119982/2026-03-22T15
