BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Concert featuring pianist Sarah Loisch
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T120000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T123000
UID:260312RLQWI4hbMECeIiZJ8gSAag
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Etfqidy3LEyCNAPyQ4UGnQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on **Monday\, March 23\, 2026\, at 12pm (Noon)** for a
  concert featuring pianist **Sarah Loisch**. This is Sarah’s second appe
 arance in our concert series\, and we know it will be a treat! The concert
  is free and open to the public\, and an offering will be collected with 5
 0% going to the performer and the other half supporting St. Mark’s Piano
  and Organ Fund. For more information\, please contact Westley at music@st
 marksevanston.org. \n\nDetails: St. Mark’s Episcopal Church (1509 Ridge
  Ave\, Evanston). Parking is limited to street parking\, but plenty is wit
 hin walking distance. \n\nMeet the performer:\n\n**Sarah Loisch** began h
 er musical studies at an early age alongside her six older siblings in Kok
 omo\, Indiana where the family’s active involvement in vocal and instrum
 ental learning led to performances across the state. Upon discovering a de
 ep connection to piano literature\, she committed to full-time musical stu
 dies and has since been an active collaborator and performer with orchestr
 as and ensembles\, including the Indiana Wind Symphony and the Heartland F
 estival Orchestra. As a performer\, Miss Loisch seeks to express the inter
 section of life and music in her work. She has made multiple concerto appe
 arances performing works by Chopin\, Rachmaninoff\, Mendelssohn\, and Sain
 t-Saëns. She is passionate about investing in the local music community a
 nd actively collaborates with Chicago musicians on recital programs\, priv
 ate events\, and other professional endeavors.\n\nIn addition to her perfo
 rmance career\, she maintains a private teaching studio where she believes
  technique and musicianship work together to foster a greater appreciation
  and love for the art of music. She was named the 2022 Top Teacher by Stei
 nway & Sons in Chicago. She completed her MA in Piano at Eastern Illinois 
 University where she studied under Dr. Victor Cayres. Previous teachers in
 clude Thomas Pandolfi and Dr. Paul Kenyon.
LOCATION:St. Mark's Episcopal Church
URL:http://www.stmarksevanston.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
