BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Folklore and Story: A Window to the Soul (Hybrid)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T143000
UID:260227KwNVI_N8rUGt5X_CgxifEQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/is2T2X5rn0OcRw-NIC3Qaw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Scholars suggest there are only a certain number of plots. If 
 accurate\, that means how different cultures tell the “same“ story pro
 vides distinct insights into the values of that tradition\, and perhaps mo
 re essentially\, offer a unique window into ourselves and our souls. Rabbi
  Michael Zedek explains how these cultural differences may really be more 
 similar than we think.
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
