BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:5th-8th Grade Caregiver Sex Education Workshop: It's That Easy
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T180000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T193000
UID:250923XW0Ze-ZLskahgU7FmvjA3A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/dUYMqomzuEeEX9EFRDZQCw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:**The "It's That Easy:" Caregiver Sex Ed Learning Session is p
 resented by YWCA/Evanston North Shore and Evanston School District 65. Th
 is virtual workshop is free for all to attend\, but registration is necess
 ary so the facilitator can plan accordingly.**\n\n**Session Description:**
 \n\nThis workshop is for parents\, caregivers\, and family members who wan
 t to deepen their knowledge about healthy sexual development\, sexual iden
 tity\, and relationships and how to discuss these topics with their childr
 en and teens. Participate in a little bit of sex ed while your students re
 ceive it in school!\n\nLed by Hallie Cohen\, Training and Prevention Coord
 inator for YWCA Evanston/North Shore and sex education consultant to D65\,
  this workshop will be an engaging\, interactive\, and discussion-based. D
 uring this workshop\, participants will:\n\n\\- Explain how their own expe
 rience with sexuality education impacts how and what they share with their
  own children\;\n\n\\- Identify the most important values and messages the
 y would like to pass on to their children about sexuality\;\n\n\\- Gain an
  understanding of healthy sexual development for their child’s age range
 \;\n\n\\- Identify teachable moments during which they can share informati
 on and family values regarding sexuality.\n\nThis workshop will be held tw
 ice\, with the focus being on different age groups. If you are unable to a
 ttend the date with the ideal focus for you\, feel free to register for th
 e other date. You will surely get a lot out of it\, and some of the materi
 al will be the same.\n\n**\\- Tuesday\, March 10\, 6-7:30 pm – (caregive
 rs of) preK-4th grade**\n\n**\\- Tuesday\, March 24\, 6-7:30 pm - (caregiv
 ers of) 5th-8th grade**\n\nPlease direct any additional questions to Halli
 e Cohen - hcohen@ywca-ens.org\n\nYou do not need to be a D65 family to att
 end\, this event is open to all!
LOCATION:YWCA Evanston North/Shore
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/5th-8th-grade-caregiver-sex-education-wor
 kshop-its-that-easy-tickets-1527604459059?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=
 attendeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebds
 shcopyurl
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
