BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Deep Dive: A Bookends University Study Group
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T180000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T193000
UID:260314NlLhwEHI9kaHZI71KQkivg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/zN2PtOS3ykyc30yWPvpfyQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:If you’re feeling overwhelmed by the constant barrage of con
 tent\, the glut of influencers and advertisers vying for your eyeballs\, a
 nd the sheer velocity and volume of daily information\, then perhaps it’
 s time to take a DEEP DIVE and reclaim your attention. Bookends University
  Deep Dive is for anyone looking to spend less time on their devices and m
 ore time thinking and discussing literature in a supportive space with oth
 ers.\n\nEvery month we’ll take a Deep Dive into a short story\, essay\, 
 or poem. No preparation necessary. We will read the text aloud together\, 
 spend some time thinking about it silently\, then use our observations to 
 really dig in to what the piece is all about. At the end of our time toget
 her\, we may even do a little optional writing inspired by the work. Deep 
 Dive is an invitation to practice sustained study in a culture often allur
 ed by convenience and speed. Let’s dive in!
LOCATION:Bookends & Beginnings
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/deep-dive-a-bookends-u
 niversity-study-group/18327440/2026-03-25T18
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
