BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stefan Hillesheim: Album Release Party w. Special Guest
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T213000
UID:260311b5ddMJ5RGU-FuWOzsa5epQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/4r9bOGXhVk-JChjicTVCUA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:This Event is the album release party for Stefan Hillesheim's 
 brand new record **"Live at the Chicago Blues Festival. "**This 10 Song li
 ve Album fully captures the energy\, joy\, and excitement of Stefan Hilles
 heim Band's performance at the 2025 Chicago Blues Festival. The record fea
 tures 8 original songs across multiple genres\, including Blues\, Southern
  Rock\, and Soul Music\, as well as 2 Songs that pay tribute to Texas Blue
 s Giant Freddy King and the King of Slide Guitar\, Elmore James. The band'
 s captivating dynamics\, crying slide guitar\, soulful vocals\, virtuoso p
 iano\, deeply emotional lyrics\, and hard-driving rhythm section will take
  you on a musical journey to Chicago's Millennium Park\, with front row se
 ats to enjoy German native Stefan Hillesheim - accompanied by some of the 
 Windy City's finest musicians - giving a truly breathtaking performance. 
 Signed LPs and CDs of "Live at the Chicago Blues Festival" will be availab
 le for purchase at the event.\n\n*"Hillesheim is both skilled and subtle i
 n equal measure."* **Living Blues Magazine**\n\n*''If this guy doesn't re
 ceive greater recognition\, there is definitely something wrong in the Cos
 mos."* **Blues Blast Magazine**\n\n*"Stefan Hillesheim is already a rising
  star who is making a big impression and attracting attention on the blues
  scene\, both here and in Europe."* **Chicago Blues Guide**\n\n*"Stefan Hi
 llesheim is one of the rising stars on the Chicago blues scene. He's a mas
 terful slide guitar player\, a strong songwriter\, and has assembled a ban
 d of talented Windy City veterans. I'm definitely keeping my eye on him fo
 r the future."* **Bruce Iglauer\, President and Founder\, Alligator Record
 s**\n\n*'At the 2025 Chicago Blues Festival\, Stefan & Co. delivered their
  customary blend of powerhouse music and professionalism\, heavy on virtuo
 sity and originals (plus a spectacular rendition of It Hurts Me Too in tr
 ibute to Stefan's hero Elmore James)."* **Dick Shurman\, Producer and Hist
 orian**\n\n***About the Artist:***\n\nStefan Hillesheim is a German native
  who made the big move across the Atlantic to chase his American Dream. In
  2014\, Stefan first arrived in Los Angeles\, California\, to attend Music
 ians Institute (GIT)\, where he was awarded Most Improved Student. Soon af
 ter\, he began to play in renowned gospel churches and live music venues a
 round the country. His signature finger-style guitar tone and driving rhyt
 hm guitar skills make Stefan a high-demand session player. During his time
  in California\, Stefan has performed and recorded with many notable artis
 ts\, including Bobby Kimball (Toto)\, Ellis Hall (Tower of Power)\, Brent 
 Carter (Average White Band)\, Emerson Cardenas (Santana)\, Frank Nitty (2P
 ac)\, and James Fortune. In 2022\, Stefan relocated to Chicago in pursuit 
 of his love of the blues. Shortly after his arrival\, Stefan formed a band
  comprised of seasoned Windy City musicians\, who perfectly complemented h
 is style\, passion\, and love for the blues. The Chicago blues community w
 elcomed Stefan with open arms - Stefan is best known for his slide guitar 
 playing\, soulful vocals\, and dynamic live performances. Stefan's main mu
 sical influences are Elmore James\, Albert King\, Jimi Hendrix\, Eric Clap
 ton\, Derek Trucks\, and Otis Redding.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://www.ticketweb.com/event/stefan-hillesheim-album-release-party-
 space-tickets/14084584
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
