 ortalimages/portalimages/XQYGic7DoE2tPp3x_R7JdA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Step into the boots of a scientist and discover more about loc
 al nature!  \n\nDid you know that the Nature Museum isn’t just an aweso
 me place to explore and learn? We’re also involved in protecting nature!
  Our resident biologists study and support the conservation efforts for a 
 variety of animals that live with us in Illinois– Blanding’s Turtles\,
  Smooth Green Snakes\, Wood Frogs\, Regal Fritillary Butterflies\, and mor
 e! \n\nJoin these scientists at the Museum on Thursday\, March 26 to exper
 ience their work first-hand! Help them find and measure snakes in our simu
 lated prairie\, dipnet in a vernal pool to find salamander eggs\, track an
 d tag turtles in our mini-marsh\, and do so much more! \n\nThis program is
  designed for all ages\, with special guidance included for how caregivers
  can best join and support their younger scientists’ experience.
LOCATION:Peggy Notebaert Nature Museum
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/conservation-celebration/
