BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Second Site Presents "The Beauty Project\," March 28 - April 4
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T190000
UID:260217jC0kCXTTjkqhrRTAOU5-0Q
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/s11IJYpS4kSMm9kjHsovvg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Second Site presents The Beauty Project\, an immersive theatri
 cal event featuring short plays and beauty demonstrations\, March 28 - Apr
 il 4. The Beauty Project\, written by Kirsten Baity\, Rachel DuBose\, Jenn
 i Lamb and Kylie Ramirez\,  is directed by Kezia Waters. \n\nThe Beauty 
 Project is an immersive theatrical experience that blends live performance
  and beauty demonstrations in a spa atmosphere. The project explores ways 
 to disentangle our ideas of beauty and self-care from “the industry\,”
  \n\nAfter six years of development\, The Beauty Project is receiving a fu
 ll production with three performances across various spaces. These seeming
 ly small issues of outward beauty speak to the big issues of our identitie
 s\, belonging\, and quality of life. This performance is made possible wit
 h contributions from 3Arts and individual donors as part of a 3AP \\(3Arts
  Projects\\) campaign.\n\nCo-Producer and Writer Rachel DuBose said\,” W
 e’re bringing four playwrights together from various backgrounds to enga
 ge in how we disentangle ourselves from the beauty industry through 10-min
 ute plays in two very different settings. But most importantly\, we’re e
 xcited to bring more care and connection to our process\, artists\, and au
 dience by setting the intention and enjoying the process.\n\nPerformances 
 on March 28 and 29 will be held at the Freyja Salon\, 4955 N Damen Ave at 
 7 p.m. Sunday April 4’s performance will take place at the Fortune House
 \, 4410 S Cottage Grove Ave. at 6:30 p.m. Tickets are on a sliding scale f
 rom $30 to “Pay What You Can” and go on sale March 1. For more informa
 tion please visit Second-Site.org.
LOCATION:Freyja Salon
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/second-site-presents-t
 he-beauty-project-march-28-april-4/18136384/2026-03-28T19
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
