BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:CHARGES (The Supplicants)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T210000
UID:260217taFd0i5gQkmlTiHn9YADNA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/O6UpYjN_h0a-UfDLfpatbw.large.png
DESCRIPTION:  Theatre Y Presents\n\nCHARGES \\(The Supplicants\\)  \n\nG
 erman title: Die Schutzbefohlenen     “those entrusted to protection
 ”       \n\nWritten by Elfriede Jelinek\n\nTranslation by Gitta Ho
 nnegar\n\nAmerican Premiere by Theatre Y \n\nA powerful elegy for the plig
 ht of refugees\, from ancient times to the present.   \n\nChicago\, IL 
 — Join us this Winter for CHARGES \\(The Supplicants\\) – Nobel Prize
  Winner Elfriede Jelinek’s Charges \\(The Supplicants\\) is a cry for th
 e displaced. Theatre Y transforms the act of seeking a home into a surreal
 ist tightrope walk teetering between gallows humor and tragedy. Originally
  written to address the global refugee crisis\, co-directors Melissa Lorra
 ine and Héctor Álvarez mine Jelinek’s text for truths about a world of
  closed borders and violent deportations.\n\n          “Nobody
  can make his own suffering sound convincing.”   – Peachum in The Thr
 eepenny Opera \n\n          “One should open one’s eyes and 
 take a new look at cruelty.”   – Friedrich Nietzsche\n\n        
   “The point of art is to show people that life is worth living by show
 ing that it isn’t.”  – Fanny Howe \n\n          “Our ra
 ft-making won’t stop the fires from flaring up\, \n\n            
                 but it may teach us how to sit with the heat witho
 ut burning away.” –Báyò Akómoláfé\n\n \n\nFebruary 26-March 29th\
 , 2026 / Thursday- Saturday 7 pm & Sundays 5 pm\n\nLocation: Theatre Y –
  3611 W Cermak Rd\, Chicago\, IL 60623 \n\nFREE and open to the public.  
 PLEASE RSVP – TICKETS: www.theatre-y.com \\( LIMITED SEATING!\\) \n\nAll
  performances are FREE to the public thanks to members who donate as littl
 e as $5/month \\($60/year\\).\n\nWe welcome DONATIONS and MEMBERS!
LOCATION:Theatre Y
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/charges-the-supplicants/2026-03-28
 /
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Improvised Jane Austen
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T203000
UID:2602124UEJtS2ySEyvISSG1qD72g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/dkHcTrk1lEuoZ2bb-OmIuA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Jane Austen’s birthday all winter long with Improv
 ised Jane Austen! Just one day cannot encapsulate a proper observation of 
 Jane Austen’s life and work. Revel with us as we extol Jane’s wit\, wo
 rk\, and vivacity.  \n\nJoin us for the rest of the winter to keep the pa
 rty going. \n\n“…countless laughs…whimsical homage to the illustriou
 s author.” — Chicago Reader \n\n“…\\[They\\] took it\, owned it an
 d created some really funny and touching moments….an evening of sillines
 s and indulgence….make running amok look like delicious fun.” — Perf
 ormInk Chicago \n\n“…Improvised Jane Austen is one of the strongest im
 prov troupes in the city. They have the ability to use Austen’s 19th cen
 tury wit and sarcasm and make it recognizable for a 21st-century audience.
 ” –Scapi Magazine \n\nEstablished in 2008\, Improvised Jane Austen is 
 a comedic ensemble that creates unscripted performances using Jane Austen
 ’s tropes\, themes\, and language to create a satirical romantic comedy 
 set in Regency-era England. Playing in Austen’s world\, Improvised Jane 
 Austen’s stories delight 21st century audiences with a modern sense and 
 sensibility. The current cast of 20\\+ performers rotate weekly\, creating
  a new ensemble for every show. Come for the humor\, stay for the heart! \
 n\nThroughout the show’s run\, Improvised Jane Austen has been Chicago R
 eader Recommended\, named a PerformInk Critics’ Pick\, voted Best sketch
 /improv troupe 2019 in the Chicago Reader’s “Best of Chicago” and wa
 s featured on WTTW playlist\, in Time Out\, the Chicago Tribune\, on WGN
 ’s Daytime Chicago and most recently on CBS News Chicago. \n\nDoors open
  at 7:00PM\, show starts at 7:30PM. \n\nLearn more: https://improvisedjane
 austen.com/
LOCATION:Mission Theater
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/improvised-jane-austen/2026-03-28/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
