SUMMARY:Elias Hix & Steinza
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T000000
UID:260224JL9kFchRGk6IvP3QA1osrA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/VGldrhVLDEuLCO9DrrDAsg.large.png
DESCRIPTION:I am Elias Hix. I grew up on a cattle farm in South Carolina. 
 I am shaped by the south's summers of thick heat and hazy air that are soo
 n followed by the cold of harsh and dry winters that leave the sky empty a
 nd hollow. Days from those seasons are trapped in my head\, with places I 
 will not go anymore\, and names that will not leave my lips.\n\nWhen I was
  15 I wrote a song called Thinner and then two years later I wrote and pro
 duced an album with that song as its title track. This album and the proje
 cts that followed are the products of the things I do not speak of anymore
  and the things I am now too scared to say. So I write them in music\, dis
 guised within the imagery and metaphors of the place I grew up in. This is
  the honest truth of my music and I hope it can help you the way it is hel
 ping me. Thank you.
LOCATION:Subterranean
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107655556?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
