BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lontalius
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T200000
UID:251211KEoBaibevUCt85omU_2URA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Fj56gzU3BEyyvc4uNzx02Q.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Jam Presents LONTALIUS with Gabby Start TUE\, 31 MAR 2026 at 0
 8:00PM CDT Ages: 18 & Over Doors Open: 07:00PM OnSale: Fri\, 5 Dec 2025 at
  11:00AM CST Announcement: Wed\, 3 Dec 2025 at 11:00AM CST Eddie Johnston\
 , aka Lontalius\, is a New Zealand singer-songwriter and producer who blen
 ds indie rock\, contemporary R&B\, and ambient music into something new. A
 cross six critically acclaimed albums exploring themes of young love\, sel
 f-discovery\, and personal growth\, he has established a distinctive\, int
 rospective voice and a reputation for emotionally resonant songwriting. Ov
 er his decade-long career\, Lontalius has performed extensively across New
  Zealand\,Australia\, Europe\, the United Kingdom\, and the United States\
 , playing his own headline shows and touring with Australian indie-pop mus
 ician Japanese Wallpaper and American emo/rap artist Nothing\, Nowhere. Al
 ong the way\, he’s won praise from BBC Radio 1\, Dazed\, The Fader\, Pop
 Matters and Stereogum.Part of a generation of musicians who grew up online
 \, while dreaming of bright lights and bigcities\, Lontalius first gained 
 international recognition in the mid-2010s for a series of Casiotone Top40
  hip-hop and R&B covers he uploaded on SoundCloud. Collaborations with Rya
 n Hemsworth and a feature on the late Virgil Abloh’s Been Trill collecti
 ve’s Electrolyte mixtape followed\, leading to the release of his debut 
 album\, I’ll Forget 17 \\(2016\\) through Brooklyn’s Partisan Records.
 / During the second half of the 2010s\, Lontalius based himself in Los Ang
 eles\, where he collaborated with Grammy Award-winning producer Om’Mas K
 eith \\(Frank Ocean\, Erykah Badu\\) and Jim Fairchild \\(Grandaddy\, Mode
 st Mouse\\). In 2019\, his signature single ‘Sleep Through Ur Alarms’ 
 beat the algorithm and broke out\, earning him a significant global audien
 ce. Over the last five years\, Lontalius has released at least one\, somet
 imes two albums a year through his PBWH label\, alongside regular singles\
 , EPs and even demo recordings. By taking the time to do the work properly
 \, he has built a timeless catalogue with an emotional range that spans lo
 -fi bedsit intimacy\, expansive stadium-ready pop singalongs\, nocturnal b
 alcony music\, and the platonic ideals of ‘90s college rock. As the endu
 ring power of his singles Comfortable\, It’s Not Love\, and All I Wanna 
 Say\, attests to\, he’s here for the long haul.
LOCATION:Martyrs'
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/833225942862665/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
