BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Third Son
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T210000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T000000
UID:260224BEq8EbnCbkGDJDbWB0z0xw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/x09SAyQSl0eNZ-EJpm0WCA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Larry Borum III\, known professionally as The Third Son\, \\(a
 ka Third\\) is a versatile producer\, singer/songwriter\, rapper\, and mul
 ti-instrumentalist hailing from Detroit\, Michigan and based in Chicago\, 
 Illinois. His music is a distinctive blend of his diverse influences\, whi
 ch span from Hip-Hop\, Jazz\, RnB\, House and Alternative Rock.\n\n​\n\n
 Third’s musical journey began early\, with his involvement in his church
  choir and his initial lessons in drums\, guitar\, and piano. During high 
 school\, he delved into music production by experimenting with loops in Ga
 rageband and creating beats with iMaschine. While studying Engineering Phy
 sics at Eastern Michigan University\, he released his first beat tape\, "B
 3AT TAPE\," on SoundCloud\, crafted entirely on his iPad. As a producer\, 
 Third has collaborated with artists such as Asaka the Renegade\, Raven\, D
 ango Forlaine\, Ronnie Alpha\, and Rose Thornberry.\n\n​\n\nHis debut al
 bum\, A Real Love Concept\, presents a groundbreaking exploration of apply
 ing the principles of electrical circuits to human relationships\, objects
 \, and the essence of love itself. Third also released his first house alb
 um in collaboration with his father Sho-nuff titled Journeys. Currently\, 
 Third is working on his next project that is expected to drop next year. \
 n\n​\n\nThird’s journey\, from his early experimentation to his debut 
 innovative album\, underscores his exceptional talent\, dedication\, and v
 ision for creating a unique musical niche.
LOCATION:Cole's Bar
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/1038067148?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=2
 87&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
