SUMMARY:A Legacy in Miniature: Rotary’s Fight to End Polio
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T170000
UID:251025ScsXCVwLUU24rPzUxw6viQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/8GVvHqDMbEewojpTxLlrXA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:**A Legacy in Miniature: Rotary’s Fight to End Polio**\n\nTo
  honor Rotary’s decades-long commitment to eradicating polio\, miniature
  artists from around the world were invited to recreate powerful moments f
 rom this historic global effort. The pieces are currently on display at On
 e Rotary Center\, and the public is invited to view the art and learn more
  about the fight to end polio worldwide.
LOCATION:One Rotary Center
URL:https://magazine.rotary.org/rotary/october_2025/MobilePagedArticle.act
 ion?articleId=2085663#articleId2085663
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
