BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pastimes D&D Weekly Play Program
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T183000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T213000
UID:260221r6rZNRpS6EeQgy99jEIgcA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/da65d06d-7dcc-441d-9865-246447d28c20.large.png
DESCRIPTION:D&D Weekly Play Campaign - Phandelver and Below: The Shattered
  Obelisk\n\nWhen:\n\nFridays at 6\;30 pm\n\nDescription:\n\nNestled on the
  northern Sword Coast\, between Neverwinter Wood and the Sword Mountains\,
  is the town of Phandalin. Centuries ago\, Phandalin was a thriving settle
 ment with deep ties to its neighboring communities. But then bandits overr
 an the town\, and Phandalin lay abandoned for centuries.\n\nOnly in the pa
 st few years have settlers built a new village on the ruins of the old. Th
 ese townsfolk hope to grow Phandalin through hard work\, camaraderie\, and
  the shared purpose of building a lasting home. Threatening their efforts 
 and their survival are bandits\, brigands\, and monsters.\n\nEvent Details
 :\n\nRegistration Link-\n\nPhandelver and Below: The Shattered Obelisk\n\n
 Start Time: 6:30 pm\n\nEntry: $10\n\nDungeon Master- Dave Quillin\n\nChara
 cter Level: 1\n\nRules: D&D 5E 2014 & 2024 rules allowed\n\nLength: 3 hour
 s\n\nTo participate\, you will need a Character Sheet and Dice.\n\nThe Dun
 geon Master is a community leader who runs the game\; their rulings are fi
 nal\, but if discrepancies occur\, an event organizer will resolve them.\n
 \nContact Information:\n\nIf you have questions\, email\n\ninfo@pastimes.n
 et\n\nor join the Pastimes Discord Server \\( \\). I recommend joining the
  discord to communicate with your DM and party members.\n\nIf you are inte
 rested in DMing a table for D&D or any Roleplaying game\, please contact o
 ur in-store event organizer:\n\ninfo@pastimes.net\n\n\\*All event details\
 , entry fees\, and prizes are subject to change.
LOCATION:Pastimes Comics & Games
URL:https://discord.gg/WQHa3mf
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:3 Stages of Love Part 2: Simple Love/Unperfect Actor
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T210000
UID:260212MIclY4hi30Wr5DW5RIwIFA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Q_7D3L9JuEWwrGXHuitJug.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Love always makes for a good story because some part of it is 
 always relatable. And what better way to explore all the various sides to 
 love than in a three-part cabaret using – at least some – words and so
 ngs that people already know. \n\n3 Stages of Love\, a semi-autobiographic
 al work devised by Ensemble Member Khnemu Menu-Ra\, features a blend of S
 hakespeare and song – along with original pieces. The full series will r
 un over the course of the season — no need to attend all three\, each pi
 ece stands alone as a complete work\, but a richer story unfolds if you se
 e the entire cycle. \n\nThe three-part series is comprised of: \n\nPart 1:
  Origins of Love: The Miseducation of Dr. K. September 2025. A sort of 
 classic “boy meets girl/meet cute” that also explores what happens nex
 t.\n\nPart 2: Simple Love/Unperfect Actor. February 2026. A coming of age
  while emotionally stunted story.\n\nPart 3 Extraordinary Love. Spring/Su
 mmer 2026. A tale that remembers the past\, embraces the present and hopes
  the future will continue to be anything but ordinary.\n\nNot familiar wit
 h cabaret as an artform? Cabaret is a form of theatrical entertainment dat
 ing back to 15th century Paris and features music song\, dance\, recitatio
 n and/or drama. The performance venue is usually a pub\, bar\, restaurant\
 , nightclub or even\, occasionally\, a casino with a space for performance
 s. The audience is often dining and drinking during the performance. Cabar
 et is often \\(but not always\\) oriented towards adult audiences with an 
 underground history. \n\nSimple Love/Unperfect Actor \\(Part 2\\) is up ne
 xt and takes place on Fridays in February \\(13\, 20 & 27\\) 2026\, at Mrs
 . Murphy & Sons Irish Bistro \\(3905 N Lincoln Ave\, Chicago\, IL 60613\\)
 . Tickets are pay-what-you-will. Reserve your spot in advance. 
LOCATION:Mrs. Murphy & Sons Irish Bistro
URL:https://www.choosechicago.com/event/3-stages-of-love-part-2-simple-lov
 e-unperfect-actor/2026-04-03/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
