BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Refracted Theatre Company Presents “Dream Hou$e\,” September 1
 2 - October 8
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T220000
UID:250829CHy8eAoY-UyqXU1STxjN9w
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/7eg-tBbLT0Ctc2DQ2dc_HA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Award-winning Refracted Theatre Company presents Dream Hou$e\,
  written by Eliana Pipes and directed by Laura Alcalá Baker\, September 1
 2 – October 18\, at the Den Theatre\, 1331 N Milwaukee Ave.  \n\nTwo si
 sters are appearing on an HGTV-style reality show to sell their family hom
 e\, hoping to capitalize on the gentrification in their “changing neighb
 orhood.” As they perform for the camera the show starts to slip into the
  surreal: one sister grapples with turmoil in the family’s ancestral pas
 t and the other learns how much she’s willing to sacrifice for the famil
 y’s future. Dream Hou$e\, which earned both the Kendeda Award and Steinb
 erg Playwriting Award in 2021\, is a crowd-pleasing comedy with a twist th
 at asks: What is the cultural cost of progress in America? And is cashing 
 in always selling out? \n\nPreviews are Friday\, Sept. 12 at 7:30 p.m.\, S
 aturday\, Sept. 13 at 7:30 p.m.\, Sunday\, Sept. 14 at 6 p.m. and Wednesda
 y\, Sept. 17 at 7:30 p.m.The regular performance schedule is Thursdays –
  Saturdays at 7:30 p.m. and Sundays at 3 p.m. Tickets go on sale Tuesday\,
  July 29 for $12 \\(previews\\) – $40\, before handling fees\, and may b
 e purchased at RefractedCo.com.
LOCATION:The Den Theatre
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/refracted-theatre-company-presents-drea
 m-houe-september-12-october-8/2026-04-03/
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jason Mayer
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T213000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T213000
UID:2603127pVFeIMGRUO3SsfUdJ0L-w
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/nykUjs3Zf02LyP3GgDEKhg.large.png
DESCRIPTION:21\\+ / www.carolspub.comBorn and raised in small town Nebrask
 a\, Jason Mayer was born to be a musician and songwriter. He started writi
 ng songs and performing for family and friends at a very young age\, and h
 is obsession for music has never stopped! He has been performing live for 
 over 15 years\, and tours extensively across the country with his band. He
  mixes country\, rock\, folk\, and roots music with a unique voice and sty
 le to make his sound unmistakable! Mayer has twice been nominated for Outs
 tanding Country Artist of the Year by the Omaha Entertainment and Arts Awa
 rds! He was also selected in 2023 as one of 15 finalists for the prestigio
 us Wild West Songwriters Festival in Deadwood\, South Dakota. He has share
 d the stage with many national artists\, including Luke Bryan\, Katy Perry
 \, Uncle Kracker\, Carly Pearce\, Craig Morgan\, Rodney Atkins\, Easton Co
 rbin\, Eli Young Band\, Maddie & Tay\, Jarrod Niemann\, Thompson Square\, 
 Morgan Evans\, Drake White\, Matt Stell\, Jimmie Allen\, David Allen Coe\,
  Aaron Watson\, Kolby Cooper\, Reckless Kelly\, Cody Canada\, Jason Boland
 \, Read Southall Band\, Josh Ward\, and many more! Mayer has released 4 or
 iginal albums with various bands over his career and has written 27 differ
 ent songs that have received radio airplay. His solo debut Old Man which w
 as penned as a tribute to his late father\, was released in the summer of 
 2021. He has since followed that up with 8 additional single releases over
  the past 4 years\, and has over one million streams across all platforms 
 on his music thus far! His most recent single Back to Nebraska was release
 d in August of 2025 and has garnered rave reviews and consistent radio air
 play. A full-length album is in the works for later in 2026! Mayer is curr
 ently on a nation-wide tour in support of his new releases! Over the past 
 3 years\, Mayer and his band have played nearly 400 shows\, covering 23 di
 fferent states and 97 different cities! Highlights include\; the MGM Grand
 \, Resorts World\, and the T Mobile Arena in Las Vegas. Losers\, Whiskey B
 ent\, Tin Roof\, and the Dawghouse in Nashville. Million Dollar Cowboy Bar
  in Jackson WY\, Grizzly Rose in Denver\, Co\, and several stops across th
 e country on the Tin Roof circuit! Live shows are high energy\, sing-along
 \, dancing fun! This event is 21 and over. Any ticket holder unable to pre
 sent valid identification indicating that they are at least 21 years of ag
 e will not be admitted to this event\, and will not be eligible for a refu
 nd.GA Tickets do not include seating. Reserved Table purchase includes ent
 rance to the show and a reserved table for the designated number of people
 .Please arrive 30 minutes prior to showtime to claim your table. If your p
 arty has not arrived by that time\, your table may be subject to be given 
 away to another group and we will do our best to facilitate your group upo
 n your arrival\, however a table is no longer guaranteed.
LOCATION:Carol's Pub
URL:https://evanstonroundtable.com/events/#/details/jason-mayer/18323122/2
 026-04-04T21
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
