 ortalimages/portalimages/QKMXhzYcvEuoH5sSA9jsVQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, April 4th at 2 PM: Gallery Talk with Joanna Pinsky\
 , Artistic Director and Cofounder of Art Encounter \n\nThe Women Painting 
 Women Exhibition expands upon our collective identities as figurative arti
 sts. In this exhibition of figure paintings\, we challenge the male gaze b
 y exploring alternative topics such as our individual selfhood\, archetypi
 cal figures and Surreal depictions of the human form. Our focus on our own
  authentic\, complex bodies provides a vehicle for change and elevates our
  position as artists. \n\nSaturday\, April 4th at 2 PM: Gallery Talk with 
 Joanna Pinsky\, Artistic Director and Cofounder of Art Encounter: \n\nArti
 sts: Melissa Arostegui\, Pochis Bank\, Gaby Bozeman\, Kate Citrin\, Jennif
 er Cronin\, Karen Fike\, Nicole Gordon\, Ellen Holtzblatt\, Sarah Kaiser\,
  Victoria Loeb\, Joanna Pinsky\, Lea Pinsky\, Mary Porterfield\, Patti Ray
 \, Nancy Rosen\, and Eleanor Spiess-Ferris.
LOCATION:Grove Gallery Evanston
