BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Before the Censors: Pre-Code Hollywood  (Hybrid)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T143000
UID:260309nRly1UMAgkCfN4WJ9WPZzQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/QkZjUJ8GtEK6bCqG1MHxDw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Between the advent of sound and the enforcement of the Motion 
 Picture Production Code censorship guidelines\, known as the Hays Code\, i
 n 1934\, American films were at their most raucous and racy where illicit 
 sex and violence were common themes. The Hays Code attempted to determine 
 what could be portrayed on screen and to promote traditional values. Autho
 r Susan Gibberman discusses some of the top movies of the era and why they
  were considered objectionable by the censors.
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The U.S. Supreme Court (Hybrid)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T113000
UID:260309MKBdcgY9jUGV8HLRqvlqDQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/DzGQ0kFmnk2zJwjJw7ZiAA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The United States is supposed to have three co-equal branches 
 of government. However\, only 8.25% of the words in the Constitution deal 
 with the judiciary branch. The Supreme Court that we know today has been c
 reated by the efforts of past Chief Justices\, principally John Marshall\,
  and the landmark 1803 Marbury vs. Madison decision. Gary Midkiff focuses 
 on the history and political dalliances of the Court\, including the 1857 
 Dred Scott decision\, the 1896 Plessy vs. Ferguson decision\, the 1954 Bro
 wn vs. Board of Education\, and the 2010 Citizens United decision.
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
