BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:PeaceBuilding Leadership Program for High Schoolers
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T180000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T200000
UID:251219WwGKBf4Pj0urqnpzBsSBtA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/-mrZu2sbUUKjpMQOtTLUaQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Anne’s Haven\, a 501\\(c\\)\\(3\\) nonprofit founded in 2016
  focused on women entrepreneurs and peacebuilding\, is launching Peacebuil
 ders\, a trailblazing and dynamic teen leadership program for high schoole
 rs. Peacebuilders runs from February through April of 2026 and consists of
  weekly sessions held on Wednesdays from 6 to 8 pm at Anne’s Haven. The 
 program is offered at no cost to students\, and a light meal will be provi
 ded during each session.\n\nFocused on building students’ leadership\, c
 ommunication\, teamwork\, and conflict resolution skills\, this program ai
 ms to inspire creative community service. Partner organizations such as BU
 ILD Chicago\, Junior Achievement of Chicago\, and Community Leadership Fel
 lows will present about topics including leadership and coalition building
 \, intercultural communication\, and restorative justice\, empowering stud
 ents to become “peacebuilders” and build more just\, peaceful communit
 ies. Students will then collaborate to create their own community service 
 events focused on some aspect of peacebuilding or community service\, unde
 r the guidance of experienced mentors. \n\nParticipation in the community
  service program may also be listed as an internship on students’ resume
 \, making them a more competitive candidate for university programs and jo
 b opportunities. Students will also be provided with “Peacebuilder” ce
 rtificates at the end of the program\, and letters of recommendation upon 
 request.\n\nThe program is directed by Jacopo DeMarinis\, a Chicago Public
  Schools teacher with a Master’s degree in Peace and Conflict Studies\, 
 and Jodi Kay\, a valued member of Anne’s Haven’s team who has a MBA fr
 om DePaul. As Janet Giangrasse\, founder and director of Anne’s Haven re
 cently noted\, “I am thrilled that Anne’s Haven is hosting Peacebuilde
 rs. Not only will this program strengthen students’ leadership and commu
 nication skills and be an invaluable addition to their resumes\, but it wi
 ll also empower them and make them more committed to community service\, w
 hich is what makes this program so unique.”\n\nTo learn more\, visit our
  program webpage here. To enroll or if you have questions\, please contact
 : jjdemarinis@gmail.com.
LOCATION:Anne's Haven
URL:http://www.anneshaven.net/peacebuilders-at-anne-s-haven.html
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
