BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lakefront Miracle: 1933 Chicago World's Fair & 1st Baseball All-St
 ar Game
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T143000
UID:260312Ljzv2MG1Ukao0mplq2v6pQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/LtH8DYXOVkCnQ8hRNUiAQw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The 1933 World’s Fair was headlined the "Century of Progress
 \," celebrating the 100 years of Chicago's existence and the progress of s
 cience and industry during that time. The fairgrounds on the lakefront\, 
 known as Rainbow City\, featured a colorful\, futuristic design that intro
 duced many to the Modernist architectural movement. Thirty-nine million vi
 sitors marveled at the new technologies and experimental materials\, inclu
 ding the first dishwasher and central air conditioning in a home. Most im
 portantly\, baseball’s first All-Star Game was held in conjunction to th
 e Fair.
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
