BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Evanston Repair Café
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T130000
UID:250418hVQbSR4as0uBisOKlvvDLA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/teDe3JnQGkm3V7zYBnDxeg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:"Never take broken for an answer" Following the Ifixit motto\,
  the Repair Café Volunteers will do their best to bring your beloved item
 s back to life... with your help!\n\nSo\, what is this all about?\n\nRepai
 r Café's are free meeting spaces where people fix things together. Beside
 s the obvious money saving\, RC's help keep stuff out of the landfill\, pr
 omote connection and collaboration\, skill-sharing and community self-reli
 ance.\n\nSo give it a try! Find that broken item you never brought yoursel
 f to throw away (remember\, there is no "away"!) and sign up for a slot th
 at matches the type or repair you need. Once at the Repair Café\, you wil
 l work together with our volunteers to repair your items.\n\nThese are our
  repair categories. Please sign up for ONE SINGLE SLOT per event. Addition
 al slots will be deleted.\n\n**Small Appliances**: Make sure you add make 
 and model when you sign up\, as well as a description of what is not worki
 ng.\n\n**Electronics**: Bring items fully charged and/or with ALL their po
 wer cords. (Printers: bring the cable that connects it to your computer!) 
 Sorry\, no TV sets or VCRs!\n\n**Sewing:** We focus on teaching you how t
 o repair\, so we do not provide alteration or tailoring services. Zippers:
  We don't replace them but we can try to repair sliders.\n\n**Jewelry**: R
 estringing\, fixing clasps or chains\, gluing\, basic cleaning and polishi
 ng We do not solder. Watch bands are not our specialty but we can try:)\n\
 n**At some of our events\, you will find additional repair categories.** C
 heck the actual sign-up to see what is available.\n\n**Bikes:** We provid
 e basic repairs such as tightening loose bolts\, loosening stuck seats and
  stems\, chain cleaning and lubing\, shifting adjustments and brake alignm
 ent. \n\n**Paper and Book Conservation**: We will be able to provide you 
 with guidelines and advice on care and maintenance for your books\, paper 
 art and photographs\, as well as direct you to local conservation and heri
 tage professionals.\n\n**Knife Sharpening:** Bring a knife or a pair of s
 cissors to have them sharpened and to learn more about blade sharpening.\n
 \n**Sock darning and Basic Visible Mending:** Bring your item and ideally
 \, the matching thread you want to use to learn how to darn your socks or 
 mend your garment. Your items must be clean\, particularly clothing\, vacu
 um cleaner hoses\, filters\, air purifiers\, toasters\, blenders...\n\n**I
 tem Assembly/Small Furniture Repair:** "Some assembly required" but you'v
 e lost the instructions? Bring it so we can work on it together. Small Fur
 niture - Fixing\, gluing\, tightening screws...\n\n**Phone Help (No Hardwa
 re Repair):** How do Google Photos and ICloud work? How do you sync your 
 Google Photos to your computer? How do you enable accessibility functions?
 \n\n**Music Instruments:** Musical guidance\, instrumental consultations 
 and suggestions. Care and repair referral suggestions for most instruments
 \, and music theory discussion and questions.\n\nSpare parts: Bring them i
 f you know them!\n\nCo-sponsored with Climate Action Evanston. We are grat
 eful to the Evanston Repair Café volunteers for their expertise\, time\, 
 and support.\n\n***The City of Evanston is committed to promoting a Citywi
 de culture of accessibility and inclusivity. To request an accommodation f
 or a program\, service\, or activity\, please call 847-866-2919 to make an
  ADA service request or fill out a request form online.***
LOCATION:Robert Crown Branch Library
URL:https://evanstonlibrary.bibliocommons.com/events/67e6e1c4605e14c9dc5db
 cdd
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
