BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Israel: Judicial or Electoral Reform (Hybrid)
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T130000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T143000
UID:260312Tf2lnkE3DU265nVjmGYBEg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/PKs4wMoO7UKNwIhAUupK7Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Moshe Pomerantz analyzes the ongoing struggle in the Israeli P
 arliament and among its citizenry over judicial reform\, and with it\, pos
 sibly a change to the country's electoral process. These are highly charge
 d and divisive issues to Israel's form of democracy and its social fabric.
  He closely examines the constitutional crisis in a country without a cons
 titution. This argument has been raging since before the October 7\, 2023 
 start of the Palestinian War.
LOCATION:North Shore Senior Center
URL:http://www.nssc.org
X-SOURCE:Evanston Roundtable
END:VEVENT
